text: Eudonia albertalis is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Harrison Gray Dyar Jr. in 1929. It is found in North America, where it has been recorded from Alberta to British Columbia, Washington, Idaho and Wyoming.Moth Photographers Group at Mississippi State University The wingspan is about 18 mm.Proceedings of the United States National Museum 74 (2768) ==References== Category:Moths described in 1929 Category:Scopariinae
title: Eudonia albertalis
